1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:04,000
FreshLedger turns receipts into freshness-aware inventory.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,730
GPT-5.6 Sol in Codex built it almost end to end.

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,500
We began with a product idea and non-negotiable safety rules.

4
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:23,500
The agent read the specification, designed the Expo, FastAPI, and SQLite architecture,
and implemented this receipt-to-ledger spine.

5
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:27,410
Local OCR returns five editable items from the photo with no cloud call.

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:34,000
GPT-5.6 Sol also built strict grounding: an item must match our shelf-life reference
before receiving advice.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:41,820
One confirmation saves the receipt and ranks the pantry by urgency,
with conservative storage guidance.

8
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:49,200
The agent then implemented rescue meals and exact, integer-cent waste accounting.

9
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:58,330
Raw chicken is most urgent; tossing it records exactly $9.44
and regenerates the recommendations from persisted inventory.

10
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:09,500
Codex connected all five promised features, while GPT-5.6 Sol traced bugs
across the client, API, database, and safety rules.

11
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:17,610
The grocery story now turns real events into spending, waste,
category breakdowns, and next-trip advice.

12
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:28,000
During adversarial review, GPT-5.6 Sol found duplicate-import, stale-advice,
compound-food, cache, and concurrency failures, then converted them into regression tests and fixes.

13
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:36,230
The result blocks this duplicate and keeps paper towels out of the food pantry.

14
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:46,000
With two receipts, FreshLedger prioritizes orange juice
and proposes meals from actual inventory.

15
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Each suggestion names what it rescues and includes safety notes.

16
00:01:51,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Choosing I made this opens an ingredient-level confirmation;
one atomic update consumes the smoothie items and refreshes every downstream view.

17
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:07,670
Codex also generated fixtures and tests that verify identity, prices,
reconciliation, and storage clamping across three standing receipts.

18
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Finally, tossing the eggs raises tracked waste to $14.63,
so advice updates from history.

19
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:29,500
GPT-5.6 Sol was FreshLedger's primary implementation engine through Codex,
driving architecture, code, tests, debugging, and review fixes.

20
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:38,810
This zero-cloud demo runs Local OCR; the optional GPT-5.6 vision path
uses the same strict Structured Outputs contract.
